00:21:28,562 --> 00:21:30,530
So, for example, the
10 gigabytes of memory.

506
00:21:30,530 --> 00:21:34,250
The memory being the RAM on
that, that's necessary for that

507
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,960
function to run.

508
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,940
If you need more than
10 gigs of RAM again,

509
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:39,440
I would argue you
probably shouldn't

510
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,550
be using Lambda as a tool.

511
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,962
It's meant for really
small, quick actions.

512
00:21:43,962 --> 00:21:45,920
You don't want to have
it spin up a whole thing

513
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:48,660
